window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>We were never supposed to fall in love. </b><b><i>We did it anyway.</i></b></p> <p><i>New York Times</i> best-selling author S.L. Scott crafts her signature heartfelt style into an epic and emotional second-chance stand-alone romance.</p> <p>I have three goals: graduate from an Ivy League university, get into medical school, and follow in my father's well-established footsteps. Everything was going exactly as planned until the local bad boy was delivered to my doorstep. <i>Literally.</i></p> <p>From the moment we meet, my old life becomes unrecognizable, but I have no regrets. I'm utterly captivated by him. <i>His smirk. His heart. His sharp wit. </i>He pushes me to live, to be wild, to pursue the dream I've always hidden inside.</p> <p>To the rest of the world, we make no sense.</p> <p><i>Me</i>, the girl from the gilded New England coast.</p> <p><i>Joshua</i>, from the small city of New Haven.</p> <p>To us, we're destiny.</p> <p>Together, we had it all. Desperately, madly in love.</p> <p><i>Until we didn't.</i></p> <p>One tragic night changed everything.</p>"; 
